


\section{How to check if an element exists with jQuery}

We can easily check if an element exists with jQuery, by using the `length` property or by checking if the selector evaluates to `true`.

\begin{codeblock}
var alength = $('#aTest').length;
log('alength', typeof alength);
alength === 0 ? log('true') : log('false');

log($('#aTest'));
\end{codeblock}


This is really not one of the areas where jQuery excels, as we could use plain Javascript

\begin{codeblock}
if(document.getElementById("myElement")) {
    //Do something...
} else {
  log('does not exist');
}
\end{codeblock}

There is a whole discussion at [stackoverflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/31044/is-there-an-exists-function-for-jquery#answer-13313296).

                                                